FBIS3-54246 "drnes016_l_94021" FBIS-NES-94-016 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 ISRAEL Man Stabbed to Death by Arab in Rishon Leziyyon TA2101073794 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 0730 GMT 21 Jan 94 TA2101073794 Tel Aviv IDF Radio Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Text] There was a stabbing attack at the Rose Garden Junction in Rishon Leziyyon this morning. A man, aged about 60, was stabbed to death by an Arab, who managed to escape. Our correspondent 'Ofer Vardi gives us more details: The incident took place a short time ago. The man who was stabbed, aged about 60, was working in his orange grove near the junction when an Arab, apparently a laborer working in the area, suddenly attacked him with a knife. The man died a few minutes later. The assailant fled, and large police forces are conducting a manhunt for him.
